🧪 Admin Tool – Test Scenarios
1. Admin Home / Landing Page
Functional
	• Verify user with valid role can access Admin Home 
	• Verify restricted users cannot access Admin Tool 
	• Validate navigation menu (Questions, Checklists, Templates, Vendors, Publishing, Audit) 
	• Verify warning prompts for high-impact changes 
Negative
	• Unauthorized role → access denied 
	• Expired session → redirect to login 

2. Select What to Author or Edit
Functional
	• Create new artifact (Question / Checklist / Template / Vendor) 
	• Edit existing artifact 
	• Review pending changes 
Edge Cases
	• Attempt to edit locked/published artifact 
	• Concurrent edits (2 users editing same item) 

3. Choose Artifact Type
Functional
	• Verify selection routes correctly: 
		○ Question → Question Authoring 
		○ Checklist → Checklist Authoring 
		○ Template → Template Authoring 
		○ Vendor → Vendor Directory 
Negative
	• No selection → block progression 

4. Authoring Screens
4.1 Question Authoring
	• Create question with: 
		○ Label 
		○ Help text 
		○ Example answer 
		○ Data type 
		○ Validation rules 
	• Validate required fields 
	• Validate data types (string, number, date, etc.) 
	• Validation rules execution 
Edge Cases
	• Invalid regex validation 
	• Long text input limits 
	• Special characters / encoding 

4.2 Checklist Authoring
	• Add steps and grouping 
	• Define dependencies between steps 
	• Assign ownership 
	• Validate Definition of Done (DoD) 
Edge Cases
	• Circular dependencies 
	• Missing required steps 
	• Invalid ownership assignment 

4.3 Template Authoring
	• Add standardized blocks 
	• Merge fields validation 
	• Preview rendering 
Edge Cases
	• Broken merge fields 
	• Missing required template variables 

4.4 Vendor Directory
	• Add vendor details 
	• Add escalation contacts 
	• Define coverage/products/status 
Edge Cases
	• Duplicate vendor entries 
	• Invalid contact formats 

5. Applicability & Conditional Logic
Functional
	• Apply logic based on: 
		○ Product 
		○ Install type 
		○ Account attributes 
	• Conditional display of questions 
	• Gating logic enforcement 
Edge Cases
	• Conflicting conditions 
	• Missing dependency data 
	• Complex nested conditions 

6. Checklist Dependencies & Automation Mapping
Functional
	• Map questions → checklist steps 
	• Configure triggers 
	• Validate sequencing 
Automation
	• Verify automatic step triggering 
	• Validate failure handling: 
		○ Fallback steps 
		○ Escalation paths 
Edge Cases
	• Broken mapping 
	• Missing dependency before execution 

7. Orchestration Map (Read-Only)
Functional
	• Verify visual representation of: 
		○ Steps 
		○ Triggers 
		○ Dependencies 
	• Validate impact analysis: 
		○ “What depends on this?” 
		○ “What breaks if changed?” 

8. Preview & Simulation
Functional
	• Preview control panel 
	• Simulate end-to-end flow 
	• Validate outbound email preview 
	• Verify vendor routing 
Edge Cases
	• Missing data in simulation 
	• Incorrect routing logic 

9. Ready to Publish Decision
Functional
	• Validate readiness checks: 
		○ Required fields complete 
		○ Dependencies valid 
	• Yes → proceed to Publish Lifecycle 
	• No → return to Edit 

10. Return to Edit
	• Verify correct screen redirection 
	• Ensure unsaved changes are handled 
	• Validate version consistency 

11. Publish Lifecycle
Functional
	• Draft → Review → Approve → Publish 
	• Versioning support 
	• Rollback / Restore functionality 
Edge Cases
	• Publish without approval 
	• Rollback to invalid version 

12. Governance, Audit & Learning
Functional
	• Track: 
		○ Who changed what 
		○ When and why 
	• Usage analytics 
	• Adoption signals 
Edge Cases
	• Missing audit logs 
	• Incorrect attribution 

🔄 End-to-End (E2E) Scenarios
Scenario 1: Full Authoring Flow
	1. Create Question 
	2. Add to Checklist 
	3. Apply conditional logic 
	4. Map dependencies 
	5. Preview & simulate 
	6. Publish 
	7. Verify in downstream system 

Scenario 2: Notification + Multi-User Flow (Important for your earlier question)
	1. User A creates checklist 
	2. Dependency triggers User B action 
	3. User B logs in 
	4. Completes assigned step 
	5. Verify: 
		○ Notification sent 
		○ Assignment updated in DB 
		○ UI reflects completion 
👉 This is where you integrate:
	• Playwright (UI) 
	• API validation (notifications) 
	• DB validation (assignment state) 

Scenario 3: Failure & Escalation
	1. Trigger failure in checklist step 
	2. Validate fallback step execution 
	3. Verify escalation routing 

